main event: A bright object, observed for five minutes, was seen in the northeastern sky traveling southeast at an elevation of 20 degrees.
interesting points: The object was described as having the intensity of a 1st Magnitude Star., The speed and altitude of the object were unknown., The observation was part of a military air report., The sighting occurred on April 1, 1964., The report mentions satellite observation related to the event.
sighted object: an object of intensity similar to a 1st Magnitude Star
